  <statement>
      
      
      <p>
          Suppose a butcher has wholesale orders from  <m>28</m>  clients.
      </p>
      
      
      <p>
          <ol>
              <li>How many ways are there to select <m>12</m>  clients  to delay their order until a future date?</li>
              <li>How many ways are there to select <m>25</m>  clients  and deliver order to them one at a time?</li>
              <li>How many ways are there to select <m>14</m>  clients  and arrange them on a waitlist for a new order?</li>
              <li>How many ways are there to select <m>9</m>  clients  to offer a special. discount to?</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
      
      
     
      
          
          
          
          
      
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      
      
      
      
     <p>
          <ol>
              <li>30421755 ways.</li>
              <li>50814724101952310083584000000 ways.</li>
              <li>3497296636753920000 ways.</li>
              <li>6906900 ways.</li>
          </ol>
          
      </p>
          
      
  </answer>
</exercise>
